== Role in Shinto ==
At [[Shinto]] shrines, large ''suzu'' often drape over the entrace, as it is said that ringing them calls gods, divinized heroes, and spirits, and allows people to acquire wholesome power and authority, while repelling evil. Handheld clustered ''suzu'', like [[Jingle bell|jingle bells]], are musically used in [[Shinto]] ceremonies. The ''suzu'' itself is said to have spiritual power, and so miniature suzu bell charms called {{Nihongo|[[omamori]]|お守り}} are offered at Shinto shrines.

